http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/%E2%80%98Focus-is-on-upgrading-skills-of-youth%E2%80%99/article13996250.ece

Finance Minister Yanamala Ramakrishnudu on Tuesday said that the State offered best working environment for investors following amendment to various labour legislations.Speaking at a discussion on ‘Changing world of work’ at the CII Partnership Summit here, he said: “By 2020, India’s average age would be 29 years, much below the other two Asian economies of Japan and China. In order to reap demographic dividends out of it, the State needed to invest in skill development and skill upgradation. In AP, there were two crore people employed in the unorganised sector. The AP Skill Development Corporation is working to impart employment oriented skills to the youth,” he stated.The plenary session was also addressed by industrialist and MP Jayadev Galla, who wanted an increase in the employability of graduates by improving the quality of education and focusing more on skill upgradation.